aVA 45-year-old man and his parakeet were involved in a single-vehicle rollover crash on Highway 26 near Banks Saturday night.\u000a\u000aBanks Fire District says they were called out to the crash at milepost 52 just before 5:30 p.m.\u000a\u000aAccording to Banks Fire Dist., the man was driving a Chevy SUV eastbound when he drifted off the right shoulder causing him to lose control of the vehicle. The SUV rolled over multiple times, crossing over into the westbound lane and coming to a rest on the shoulder.\u000a\u000aA female passerby, who happened to be an employee at a Portland veterinarian clinic, heard the man voicing concern over his parakeet that was traveling with him.\u000a\u000aThe parakeet was found still in its cage. The vet worker took the bird in for an evaluation and will be keeping the bird until the owner can reclaim him.\u000a\u000aThe driver was taken to Emanuel Hospital and he is said to be in stable condition.\u000a\u000aThe cause of the accident is under investigation.\u000a\u000aDrivers should expect some delays on Highway 26 near milepost 52.\u000a\u000aCopyright 2017 KPTV-KPDX Broadcasting Corporation. All rights reserved.
